review_blob: i love the tart meads. balanced. not painfully tart, still tightens the cheeks. beautiful color, as always with superstition.
even stronger and rougher than the lagrimas de pro. another wonderful dry raw mead. you feel it, warm, strong. beautiful color, smooth.
i love the dry meads. this mead is dry and rough like a whiskey. you taste it, it makes you warm. i love this mead. simple. good.
beer_name: Superstition Lagrimas de Oro (Tears of Gold) Mead

review_blob: the best balanced mead superstition has made. a balance between the sweet and the tart. dark and smooth. smells like heaven. perfection. great work jeff and carlos.
so perfect. i love the tart tart ciders...and now there is a mead. tart sweet balanced red. oh superstition, you do it right.
strawberry has its day! the most beautiful rusty deep pink color. sweet, delicious strawberry goodness.
sweet. beautiful. no need for desert. as sweet as superstition gets and as complex.
i clearly LOVE this mead. my first love at superstition...i adore the desert, and this mead tastes like the desert in love. pure beauty.
hands down one of my favorite superstition meads. the sweet grape aroma is delicious. taste the grape!
nice true vanilla flavor. would be wonderful for a sweet white wine lover.
